    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "TOLEDO, Ohio \u2013 The Toledo baseball team dropped the middle game of a three-game MAC series against Northern Illinois, falling to the Huskies, 8-3 at Scott Park on Saturday.\nThe loss snaps the Rockets'\u00a0(8-9, 4-1 MAC) five-game winning streak. The Huskies (10-6, 2-3 MAC) scored five runs in the top of the fourth inning to take a 6-1 lead and held the lead the rest of the way. Toledo cut the deficit to 6-3 in the eighth, but two more NIU runs crossed the plate in the ninth.\nFor Toledo,\nAlex McCranie\nhad a 3-for-5 game with two doubles, an RBI and a run scored.\nCharlie Scholvin\nscored two runs while\nTroy Sudbrook\nand\nCole Cahill\neach supplied an RBI.\nStarter\nDeron Swanson\n(2-2) took the losing decision.\nNate Langbehn\npitched 3.0 scoreless and hitless innings.\nSunday's finale will decide the series winner. First pitch is at 1:00 p.m.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"We didn't play very well today across the board. As we've been winning, we've been able to stack good at-bats together and build some innings to score. We didn't get that done today. We couldn't prevent the big inning when they got five runs in the fourth. Very disappointing day after we've played some really good baseball. The key for this group is simple \u2013 can they be consistent day-in and day-out doing the things it takes to win games. We need to come tomorrow ready to play and win the series.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nAlex McCranie\n\u2013 3-for-5, 1 RBI, 1 run, 2 2B\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 1-for-3, 1 RBP, 1 HBP\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 2 runs, 2 walks\nPitching Lines\nDeron Swanson\n(L, 2-2) \u2013 5.0 IP, 7 H, 6 R, 5 ER, 2 BB, 3 Ks\nNate Langbehn\n\u2013 3.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 3 BB, 4 Ks\nHow it Happened\nTroy Sudbrook\nopened the scoring with an RBI single in the first. An NIU sac fly in the third tied things, 1-1.\nIn the top of the fourth, three RBI singles and a sacrifice fly led to a five-running inning for NIU and a 6-1 Huskies' lead.\nToledo brought home runs in the fifth and eighth on\nAlex McCranie's\nRBI double and\nCole Cahill's\nRBI single to cut the deficit to 6-3.\nNorthern Illinois' Caden Robertson hit a two-run home run in the top of the ninth to extend NIU's lead to 8-3."
